  "source": "{title: Top Of The World}\n{artist: Carpenters}\n{key: C}\n{reviewed: false}\n\n{section: Verse 1}\n[C]Such a [G7]feelings coming [C]over me\n[Em]           [Dm]    [G7]   [C]   [C7]\n\n[F]Not a [G7]cloud in the sky\n[Em]Got the [Am]sun in my eyes\n[Dm]And I won't be [G7]surprised if it's a dream\n[C]Everything I [G7]want the [C]world to be\n[Em]    [Dm]   [G7]  [C]   [C7]\nIs now coming [F]true [G7]especially [Em]for [Am]me\n[Dm]And the reason is [G7]clear, it's because you are here\n[Dm]You're the nearest thing to [G7]heaven that I've seen\n\n{section: Chorus}\n[C]I'm on the [C7]top of the [F]world looking down on creation\n[C]And the [G7]only explanation [C]I [C7]can find\n[F]Is the [G7]love that I've [C]found ever [F]since you've been around\n[C]Your [G7]love's put me [C]at the top of the world\n\n{section: Verse 2}\nSomething in the wind has learned my name\nAnd it's telling me that things are not the same\nIn the leaves on the trees\nAnd the touch of the breeze\nThere's a pleasing sense of happiness for me\nThere is only one wish on my mind\nWhen this day is through I hope that I will find\nThat tomorrow will be just the same for you and me\nAll I need will be mine if you are here\n"
